@startuml 12A-state-user-account
' CVerify — User account lifecycle (users.Status, native PG enum "user_status")
' Verified against:
'   Modules/Shared/Domain/Enums/UserStatus.cs                (6 PgName values)
'   Modules/Shared/Domain/Entities/User.cs:80-130            (TransitionTo — the authoritative guard table)
'   Modules/Auth/Services/AuthService.cs
'       :375,:996,:2618  new User { Status = EMAIL_VERIFY_PENDING }   (OAuth / register / link flows)
'       :3973-3977       ActivateUserAsync -> TransitionTo(ACTIVE)
'       :1120            VerifyEmailAsync -> ActivateUserAsync
'       :395,:472,:2624,:2633  OAuth callback -> ActivateUserAsync
'       :1538 DeleteMeAsync            -> user.Status = DELETED  (direct assignment)
'       :1631 InitiateDeletionAsync    -> TransitionTo(DELETION_PENDING) at :1735
'       :1803 ReactivateAccountAsync   -> TransitionTo(ACTIVE) at :1824
'       :180  LoginAsync — DELETION_PENDING short-circuits to a REACTIVATE next-step
'   Modules/Recovery/Services/RecoveryExecutionEngine.cs:49 ExecuteOptionAAsync -> TransitionTo(ACTIVE) :124
'                                                      :262 ExecuteOptionBAsync -> TransitionTo(ACTIVE) :404
'   Modules/Shared/System/BackgroundWorkers/TokenCleanupBackgroundJob.cs:252,:326 (14-day hard purge)
'   Modules/Auth/Services/IdentityStateResolver.cs:97-98 · Modules/Auth/Services/AccountService.cs:61
'   docs/architecture/reverse-engineered/GROUND-TRUTH.md  §4 (user_status is the ONLY native PG enum)

title users.Status — UserStatus (native PostgreSQL enum "user_status")

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor<<terminal>> #FFECEC
}

[*] --> EMAIL_VERIFY_PENDING : AuthService.RegisterAsync\n(new User { Status = EMAIL_VERIFY_PENDING })

state EMAIL_VERIFY_PENDING
state ACTIVE
state SUSPENDED
state BANNED
state DELETION_PENDING
state DELETED <<terminal>>

EMAIL_VERIFY_PENDING --> ACTIVE : VerifyEmailAsync -> ActivateUserAsync\n(TransitionTo(ACTIVE))
EMAIL_VERIFY_PENDING --> ACTIVE : OAuth callback with verified provider email\n-> ActivateUserAsync
EMAIL_VERIFY_PENDING --> DELETION_PENDING : InitiateDeletionAsync
EMAIL_VERIFY_PENDING --> DELETED : DeleteMeAsync

ACTIVE --> SUSPENDED : <i>allowed by TransitionTo</i>
ACTIVE --> BANNED : <i>allowed by TransitionTo</i>
ACTIVE --> DELETION_PENDING : AuthService.InitiateDeletionAsync\n(TransitionTo, inside a DB transaction;\nsets DeletedAt, SessionVersion++)
ACTIVE --> DELETED : AuthService.DeleteMeAsync

SUSPENDED --> ACTIVE : <i>allowed by TransitionTo</i>
SUSPENDED --> BANNED : <i>allowed by TransitionTo</i>
SUSPENDED --> DELETION_PENDING : InitiateDeletionAsync
SUSPENDED --> DELETED : DeleteMeAsync

BANNED --> ACTIVE : <i>allowed by TransitionTo</i>
BANNED --> DELETION_PENDING : InitiateDeletionAsync
BANNED --> DELETED : DeleteMeAsync

DELETION_PENDING --> ACTIVE : <b>AuthService.ReactivateAccountAsync</b>\n(TransitionTo(ACTIVE); DeletedAt = null; SessionVersion++)
DELETION_PENDING --> DELETED : <i>allowed by TransitionTo</i>

DELETION_PENDING --> [*] : TokenCleanupBackgroundJob (hourly)\nDeletedAt <= now-14d -> context.Users.Remove(user)\n<b>hard delete, batches of 50</b>

DELETED --> [*]

note right of DELETION_PENDING
  <b>Reactivation path</b>
  LoginAsync (AuthService.cs:180) detects Status = DELETION_PENDING,
  caches `reactivate:token:{t}` in Redis for 10 minutes and returns a
  next-step response `REACTIVATE:{token}` instead of issuing tokens.
  ReactivateAccountAsync consumes that token, requires the user to still
  be DELETION_PENDING, and un-soft-deletes the AuthProvider rows too.
end note

note right of ACTIVE
  RecoveryExecutionEngine.ExecuteOptionAAsync / ExecuteOptionBAsync
  also call TransitionTo(ACTIVE) when an organization recovery
  reinstates a representative's user account.
end note

note bottom of EMAIL_VERIFY_PENDING
  ⚠ There is NO EMAIL_VERIFY_PENDING -> SUSPENDED or -> BANNED transition
  in TransitionTo. A pending-verification account cannot be suspended
  or banned without first being activated.
end note

note as N_GUARD
  <b>Guard, User.cs:86</b>
  TransitionTo throws InvalidOperationException when the target is
  DELETION_PENDING and IsLegalHold is true:
  "Cannot initiate account deletion when a legal or compliance hold
  is active on this account."
  Any transition not in the switch table also throws.
end note

note as N_DISCREPANCY #FFF0F0
  <b>Discrepancies recorded</b>
  1. AuthService.DeleteMeAsync (:1557) assigns
     <b>user.Status = UserStatus.DELETED</b> directly, bypassing
     TransitionTo — its own comment says "setting DELETED directly
     for legacy test compatibility". The IsLegalHold guard is therefore
     NOT applied on that path, unlike InitiateDeletionAsync.
  2. No production code path was found that WRITES SUSPENDED or BANNED.
     Both are only ever READ (IdentityStateResolver.cs:97-98,
     AccountService.cs:61, TrustEngineService.cs:90). The transitions
     into them are drawn as "allowed by TransitionTo" because that is
     the only evidence for them.
end note

@enduml
